        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "Trouble has a way of finding your...or maybe you really just like finding it. It's hard to tell. You were just a newspaper guy, working your beat in the hard streets of Baltimore, when your sire found you. You figured he was one of the kooks you ran into in your line of work, and you kind of liked him. It turned out he was a Tremere vampire, however, who liked the way your mind worked. He embraced you and sent you to Vienna for training, where you met another new Embrace, Tara Elliot. The two of you were partnered up when you were released on your own, sent to Washington D.C. to serve in Octagon House under Pontifex Dorfman, in the court of Marcus Vital. The adventures were many with Tara (including one notable instance with some technocratic mages and a run in with an Inquisition Hunter named Tim Milner, who is now a member of Clan Giovanni). You and Tara had a falling out, however, after one particular mission where you felt she broke the code, even if she was trying to save you. Because she was of a lower generation and more influence, she was not reprimanded, but you were punished. Not only did you lose your one friend you had in the clan at the time, you had to do grunt work in chantries like Atlanta. It took you some time to climb your way back into the good graces of your superiors, mostly because...well, you've never exactly been one to conform totally, and you remember that thing about trouble? You tend to get into all sorts of scrapes, even if you don't mean it. Which, in the end, is perhaps why it's good you connected with Tara in the end and made up, because she's been able to smooth your way a bit, thanks to being a Regent (and a Quaestor, but that's besides the point). Still, your reputation, and your vast experience handling sticky situations, means you are the perfect person for the Tremere to send into problem areas, like Los Angeles. You've heard rumors floating around for a while regarding Los Angeles, it's chantry, and the Tremere Prince, but there are other things going on, political things, involving one Pontifex Bey. All you've heard is rumors, and you personally have no opinion on this matter, though Tara's warned you to tred carefully here (or, in her words, \"Don't make me come in there and save your ass.\"). You are here to see just what the clan is up to and report to your superiors on what is going on with the clan and of course decide just how much trouble you can get yourself in to in Los Angeles. (Note, come talk to Jenn or Patric if you are playing this character to get a brief backstory.)"
        ],
